          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <placeName>Macon Geo</placeName>
                                        <date>July 16 1849</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">I received this morning<lb/> the last Occident;
                                        but as I do not find my name among the<lb/> receipt, I
                                        apprehend that you have not received my subscription<lb/>
                                        yet. <persName>Mr Elias Block</persName> formerly from
                                                  <placeName>Griffin</placeName> called on me<lb/>
                                        when he was about removing to
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> on the
                                                  <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of May</date><lb/>
                                        and I sent with him the Three Dollars. I request you
                                        respectfully<lb/> to cause an inquiry after him,
                                                  <persName>Mrsses Blum</persName> &amp;
                                                  <persName>Simpson</persName> or<lb/>
                                        <persName>Arnolds</persName> could tell you where to find
                                        him.</p>
                              <p>Be so kind as to remember me to <persName>Mr.
                                        Hackenburg</persName>, I read<lb/> with sorrow the demise of
                                        his son <persName>Henry</persName>. Give him my<lb/> care,
                                        May the Lord remember him to good, and may he be<lb/>
                                        consoled! I am your admirer and</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Brother in faith</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">A. Defsan</persName>.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <hi rend="underline">past paid</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Pa.</placeName>
                              </p>
